An evergreen climber or creeper commonly found on trees or walls as well as old houses. Sometimes cultivated. The leaves are of 2 types: the palmately five-lobed juvenile leaves on creeping and climbing stems, and the unlobed cordate adult leaves on fertile flowering stems exposed to full sun, usually high in the crowns of trees or the top of rock faces.. Flowers green.
